title: Version 2.2b5 unable to analyze videos after training (get_nframes_robust()/ffprobe)
body:
OS: Windows 10
DeepLabCut Version: 2.2b5
Anaconda env used: DLC-GPU

Hi! I've just started to transition to version 2.2 for multi-animal tracking. I've been working almost entirely within the Project Manager (though I previously used older versions of DLC in a jupyter notebook).

I set up my first multi-animal project and it seemed to be going smoothly through the evaluate network stage. After evaluate it successfully made the example maps. When I went to analyze the videos, however, I started getting an error and I don't know what to make of it. Thanks for any help you can provide!

I'm not sure if it's relevant or a separate issue, but I also had some issues with the skeleton (it said "no fully labelled animal was found") but thought it might still work since the training/evaluation seemed ok. If you think I need to go back and resolve that first, let me know!
